12:55:40','Dr Shari Trimble\nRegistered Osteopath, Biodynamic Craniosacral Osteopath, Prescriptive Exercise Consultant\nM.H.Sc. [Osteo], B.Sc [Clin], Member of A.O.A\n\nMONDAY 1pm - 7pm\nWEDNESDAY 1pm - 7pm\nFRIDAY 1pm - 6pm\n\nShari is the co owner of the practice with Camille de Niese. She has worked in the health and manual medicine field for more than 15 years and also lectures in anatomy, pathology and clinical skills.\n\nSharis passion is to assist in helping the body\'s own wisdom restore health and balance. With a nurturing and gentle style, Shari tailors her treatments to each individual, working to stimulate the body\'s natural ability to heal itself.\n<h3><strong>Special Interest in Yoga and Performance Arts</strong></h3>\nWith her past experience in engineering, a Bachelor degree in Clinical Science and a Masters in Osteopathy, Shari has a thorough understanding of body mechanics and a unique capacity to view your injury in the context of activity and training. Shari focuses on helping you to rehabilitate your injury whilst continuing to practice and train, and how to avoid further disruption to your program.\n\nCurrently a member of the Footscray Womens Circus Shari also runs her dogs and practices yoga daily. She has a background in dance, pilates and long distance running and has completed postgraduate studies in exercise prescription &amp; clinical pilates.\n<h3><strong>Special Interests in Womens Health, Fertility &amp; Children</strong></h3>\nShari has completed post graduate osteopathic studies in obstetrics &amp; gynaecology and the treatment of children and enjoys working with the challenges women may face during pregnancy and motherhood.\n<h3><strong><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-255\" src=\"http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/pregnancy.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"266\" height=\"266\" />Pregnancy</strong></h3>\nDuring pregnancy there are many physiological processes that take place and large changes to a womens body occur in a relatively short space of time. A hormone called Relaxin softens the ligaments around the joints of the pelvis which is a natural process and assists childbirth. However for some women this process can cause the joints of the pelvis to loosen too much and can result in the pelvis becoming unstable or out of alignment and in a susceptible women can contribute to low back and pelvic pain.\n\nPost pregnancy there will be pressure on different areas such as the upper back and neck. This may be due to poor posture during breast feeding and incorrect lifting techniques. Osteopathic treatment and corrective muscle re-education can aid in the way the body copes with these pressures.\n<h3><strong>Babies &amp; Children</strong></h3>\nA baby will often communicate there is a problem by being unsettled, irritable or wakeful. Symptoms in a newborn baby to be aware of are:\n<ul>\n	<li>Colic</li>\n	<li>excessive wind</li>\n	<li>continuous crying</li>\n	<li>difficulty feeding or a preference to feed from one breast</li>\n	<li>sleeping difficulties</li>\n	<li>stiffness of the neck muscles</li>\n	<li>favouring the head to one side</li>\n	<li>a misshapen head</li>\n</ul>\n<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-257\" src=\"http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/osteopathy-for-infants1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"228\" height=\"235\" />Biodynamic/Cranial Osteopathy can be useful in treating a wide range of symptoms and conditions in children including the following\n<ul>\n	<li>back and neck pain</li>\n	<li>ear infections and glue ear</li>\n	<li>growing pains</li>\n	<li>headaches</li>\n	<li>behavioural problems</li>\n	<li>hyperactivity</li>\n	<li>speech problems</li>\n</ul>\nServices Offered:\n<ul>\n	<li><a title=\"Read About Osteopathy\" href=\"/services/osteopathy\">Osteopathy</a></li>\n	<li><a href=\"/services/biodynamic-cranial-osteopathy\">Biodynamics/Cranial Osteopathy</a></li>\n</ul>','Shari Trimble','','inherit','open','open','','45-autosave','','','2011-02-12 22:55:40','2011-02-12 12:55:40','',45,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/%post_name%',0,'revision','',0),(107,1,'2011-03-10 19:48:09','2011-03-10 09:48:09','Here are our services:\n<ul>\n	<li><a href=\"/services/osteopathy\">Osteopathy</a></li>\n	<li><a href=\"/services/biodynamic-cranial-osteopathy\">Biodynamic/Cranial Osteopathy</a></li>\n	<li><a href=\"/services/remedial-massage\">Remedial Massage</a></li>\n	<li><a href=\"/services/kinesiology\">Kinesiology</a></li>\n	<li>Myotherapy</li>\n	<li><a href=\"/services/acupuncturetcm\">Acupuncture/Traditional Chinese Medicine</a></li>\n	<li><a href=\"/services/naturopathy\">Naturopathy</a></li>\n</ul>','Services','','inherit','open','open','','32-autosave','','','2011-03-10 19:48:09','2011-03-10 09:48:09','',32,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/%post_name%',0,'revision','',0),(108,1,'2009-10-06 21:43:38','2009-10-06 11:43:38','','Services','','inherit','open','open','','32-revision-3','','','2009-10-06 21:43:38','2009-10-06 11:43:38','',32,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/%post_name%',0,'revision','',0),(109,1,'2009-10-07 00:25:10','2009-10-06 14:25:10','sdfsdfsd\r\n<!--more-->','Services','','inherit','open','open','','32-revision-4','','','2009-10-07 00:25:10','2009-10-06 14:25:10','',32,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/%post_name%',0,'revision','',0),(117,1,'2009-10-07 00:41:50','2009-10-06 14:41:50','<ul></ul>','Services','','inherit','open','open','','32-revision-11','','','2009-10-07 00:41:50','2009-10-06 14:41:50','',32,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/%post_name%',0,'revision','',0),(146,1,'2009-10-07 22:58:29','2009-10-07 12:58:29','<code> </code>\r\n<ul></ul>','Services','','inherit','open','open','','32-revision-14','','','2009-10-07 22:58:29','2009-10-07 12:58:29','',32,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/32-revision-14',0,'revision','',0),(118,1,'2009-10-07 00:41:58','2009-10-06 14:41:58','<ul>\r\n<?php wp_list_pages(\'title_li=\'); ?>\r\n</ul>','Services','','inherit','open','open','','32-revision-12','','','2009-10-07 00:41:58','2009-10-06 14:41:58','',32,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/%post_name%',0,'revision','',0),(120,1,'2009-10-07 00:57:34','2009-10-06 14:57:34','','Osteopathy','','inherit','open','open','','119-revision','','','2009-10-07 00:57:34','2009-10-06 14:57:34','',119,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/%post_name%',0,'revision','',0),(121,1,'2009-10-17 21:18:37','2009-10-17 11:18:37','Osteopathy is a holistic based treatment using the hands to correct tissue &amp; joint abnormalities. It is aimed at restoring physical &amp; mental wellbeing and thereby making it easier for the body to use its own recuperative powers to heal itself. The treatment goal is to improve circulation, reduce muscle spasm, improve flexibility, maintain nerve supply &amp; restore muscle/joint harmony. Along with the general musculoskeletal problems such as back/neck pain, osteopathy can help with a wide variety of problems including postural changes during pregnancy; babies with colic or sleeplessness, repetitive strain injury, postural problems caused by driving or work strain, the pain of arthritis and sports injuries among many others.\n\n<a title=\"Read More About Osteopathy\" href=\"/services/osteopathy\">Read More</a>...','Osteopathy','','inherit','open','open','','119-autosave','','','2009-10-17 21:18:37','2009-10-17 11:18:37','',119,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/%post_name%',0,'revision','',0),(122,1,'2009-10-07 01:00:07','2009-10-06 15:00:07','','osteopathy','','inherit','open','open','','osteopathy-2','','','2009-10-07 01:00:07','2009-10-06 15:00:07','',119,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/osteopathy.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(110,1,'2009-10-07 00:25:43','2009-10-06 14:25:43','Osteopathy is a holistic based treatment using the hands to correct tissue & joint abnormalities. It is aimed at restoring physical & mental wellbeing and thereby making it easier for the body to use its own recuperative powers to heal itself. The treatment goal is to improve circulation, reduce muscle spasm, improve flexibility, maintain nerve supply & restore muscle/joint harmony. Along with the general musculoskeletal problems such as back/neck pain, osteopathy can help with a wide variety of problems including postural changes during pregnancy; babies with colic or sleeplessness, repetitive strain injury, postural problems caused by driving or work strain, the pain of arthritis and sports injuries among many others.\r\n\r\nOsteopaths work with their hands using a wide variety of treatment techniques such as:\r\n\r\n    * Massage and stretching techniques\r\n    * Articulation techniques, in which joints are mobilised by being passively taken through their range of motion\r\n    * Muscle Energy techniques, in which contracted muscles are released by alternately being stretched and made to work against resistance.\r\n    * Positional Release Techniques, which achieve release of restriction by placing the affected joint or muscle in a position of comfort, while applying a stretching release to the opposing muscles.\r\n    * Functional techniques, which involve gentle mobilisation of joints in a way which nudges barriers to normal movement until a way is found through the restriction\r\n    * Manipulation, which may be used where it is appropriate and safe to do so, though it is not the mainstay of most Osteopathic treatments. Osteopathic manipulations are carried out using minimum force levels in order to maximise safety and minimise patient discomfort\r\n    * Many Osteopaths also use what is known as cranial technique, which is a gentle release technique particularly, suited to young children and the physically frail.\r\n    * Visceral techniques are used in the management of conditions affecting internal organs. These involve gentle and rhythmical stretching of the visceral areas\r\n\r\n<!--more-->','Services','','inherit','open','open','','32-revision-5','','','2009