','','32-revision-15','','','2009-10-07 22:58:51','2009-10-07 12:58:51','',32,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/32-revision-15',0,'revision','',0),(170,1,'2009-10-06 21:43:53','2009-10-06 11:43:53','','Practioners','','inherit','open','open','','43-revision-4','','','2009-10-06 21:43:53','2009-10-06 11:43:53','',43,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/43-revision-4',0,'revision','',0),(208,1,'2011-03-10 19:58:48','2011-03-10 09:58:48','Our Staff:\n<ul>\n	<li>Shari Trimble (Biodynamic Osteopathy)</li>\n	<li>Camille de Niese (Kinesiology/Remedial Massage)</li>\n	<li>Carly Richardson (Office Manager)</li>\n	<li>Anne Howard (Naturopathy)</li>\n	<li>Chris Eddy (Acupuncture/Traditional Chinese Medicine)</li>\n	<li>Santos Martinez (Myotherapist)</li>\n	<li>Anna-Mai Hoek (Remedial Massage)</li>\n	<li>Paul Turner (Biodynamic Osteopathy)</li>\n</ul>','Our Team','','inherit','open','open','','43-autosave','','','2011-03-10 19:58:48','2011-03-10 09:58:48','',43,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/43-autosave',0,'revision','',0),(171,1,'2009-10-07 01:08:58','2009-10-06 15:08:58','[caption id=\"attachment_103\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"337\" caption=\"Dr Shari Trimble\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-103\" title=\"Dr Shari Trimble\" src=\"http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/shari.jpg\" alt=\"Dr Shari Trimble\" width=\"337\" height=\"434\" />[/caption]\r\n\r\nDr Shari Trimble\r\nOsteopath, Prescriptive Exercise Consultant\r\nM.H.Sc. [Osteo], B.Sc [Clin], M.C.O.C.A\r\n\r\nMONDAY 1pm - 7pm\r\nWEDNESDAY 1pm - 7pm\r\nFRIDAY 3:15pm - 6:30pm\r\n\r\nServices Offered:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Read About Osteopathy\" href=\"/services/osteopathy\">Osteopathy</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Shari Trimble','','inherit','open','open','','45-revision-9','','','2009-10-07 01:08:58','2009-10-06 15:08:58','',45,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/45-revision-9',0,'revision','',0),(172,1,'2009-10-17 17:52:28','2009-10-17 07:52:28','[caption id=\"attachment_103\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"256\" caption=\"Dr Shari Trimble\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-103\" title=\"Dr Shari Trimble\" src=\"http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/shari.jpg\" alt=\"Dr Shari Trimble\" width=\"256\" height=\"329\" />[/caption]\r\n\r\nDr Shari Trimble\r\nOsteopath, Prescriptive Exercise Consultant\r\nM.H.Sc. [Osteo], B.Sc [Clin], M.C.O.C.A\r\n\r\nMONDAY 1pm - 7pm\r\nWEDNESDAY 1pm - 7pm\r\nFRIDAY 3:15pm - 6:30pm\r\n\r\nShari is the co owner of the practice with Camille de Niese. She has worked in the health and manual medicine field for more than 15 years and also lectures in anatomy, pathology and clinical skills.\r\n\r\nSharis passion is to assist in helping the body\'s own wisdom restore health and balance. With a nurturing and gentle style, Shari tailors her treatments to each individual, working to stimulate the body\'s natural ability to heal itself.\r\n\r\n<strong>Special Interest in Yoga and Performance Arts</strong>\r\n\r\nWith her past experience in engineering, a Bachelor degree in Clinical Science and a Masters in Osteopathy, Shari has a thorough understanding of body mechanics and a unique capacity to view your injury in the context of activity and training. Shari focuses on helping you to rehabilitate your injury whilst continuing to practice and train, and how to avoid further disruption to your program.\r\n\r\nCurrently a member of the Footscray Womens Circus Shari also runs her dogs and practices yoga daily. She has a background in dance, pilates and long distance running and has completed postgraduate studies in exercise prescription &amp; clinical pilates.\r\n\r\n<strong>Special Interests in Womens Health, Fertility &amp; Children</strong>\r\n\r\nShari has completed post graduate osteopathic studies in obstetrics &amp; gynaecology and the treatment of children and enjoys working with the challenges women may face during pregnancy and motherhood.\r\n\r\n<strong>Pregnancy</strong>\r\n\r\nDuring pregnancy there are many physiological processes that take place and large changes to a womens body occur in a relatively short space of time. A hormone called Relaxin softens the ligaments around the joints of the pelvis which is a natural process and assists childbirth. However for some women this process can cause the joints of the pelvis to loosen too much and can result in the pelvis becoming unstable or out of alignment and in a susceptible women can contribute to low back and pelvic pain.\r\n\r\nPost pregnancy there will be pressure on different areas such as the upper back and neck. This may be due to poor posture during breast feeding and incorrect lifting techniques. Osteopathic treatment and corrective muscle re-education can aid in the way the body copes with these pressures.\r\n\r\n<strong>Babies &amp; Children</strong>\r\n\r\nA baby will often communicate there is a problem by being unsettled, irritable or wakeful. Symptoms in a newborn baby to be aware of are:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Colic</li>\r\n	<li>excessive wind</li>\r\n	<li>continuous crying</li>\r\n	<li>difficulty feeding or a preference to feed from one breast</li>\r\n	<li>sleeping difficulties</li>\r\n	<li>stiffness of the neck muscles</li>\r\n	<li>favouring the head to one side</li>\r\n	<li>a misshapen head</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nBiodynamic/Cranial Osteopathy can be useful in treating a wide range of symptoms and conditions in children including the following\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>back and neck pain</li>\r\n	<li>ear infections and glue ear</li>\r\n	<li>growing pains</li>\r\n	<li>headaches</li>\r\n	<li>behavioural problems</li>\r\n	<li>hyperactivity</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nspeech problems\r\n\r\nServices Offered:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Read About Osteopathy\" href=\"/services/osteopathy\">Osteopathy</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Shari Trimble','','inherit','open','open','','45-revision-10','','','2009-10-17 17:52:28','2009-10-17 07:52:28','',45,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/45-revision-10',0,'revision','',0),(173,1,'2009-10-17 17:54:17','2009-10-17 07:54:17','<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-176\" src=\"http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/sarah.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"232\" height=\"251\" />profile coming soon...','Sarah Valentini','','draft','open','open','','sarah-valentini','','','2011-03-10 19:51:45','2011-03-10 09:51:45','',43,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/?page_id=173',3,'page','',0),(174,1,'2009-10-17 17:54:06','2009-10-17 07:54:06','','Sarah Valentini','','inherit','open','open','','173-revision','','','2009-10-17 17:54:06','2009-10-17 07:54:06','',173,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/173-revision',0,'revision','',0),(175,1,'2009-10-17 17:54:17','2009-10-17 07:54:17','profile coming soon...','Sarah Valentini','','inherit','open','open','','173-revision-2','','','2009-10-17 17:54:17','2009-10-17 07:54:17','',173,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/173-revision-2',0,'revision','',0),(176,1,'2009-10-17 17:55:54','2009-10-17 07:55:54','','sarah','','inherit','open','open','','sarah','','','2009-10-17 17:55:54','2009-10-17 07:55:54','',173,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/sarah.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(177,1,'2009-10-17 17:54:57','2009-10-17 07:54:57','profile coming soon...','Sarah Valentini','','inherit','open','open','','173-revision-3','','','2009-10-17 17:54:57','2009-10-17 07:54:57','',173,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/173-revision-3',0,'revision','',0),(178,1,'2009-10-06 23:32:33','2009-10-06 13:32:33','Dip.H.Sc. in Remedial Therapy\r\nDip. Anatomy, Physiology & Massage [London]\r\nITEC Dip Massage [London]\r\nAAMT, ANTA, AKA (student member), Network Fitness\r\n\r\nWEDNESDAY 12pm - 7:15pm\r\nTHURSDAY 12pm - 7:15pm\r\nFRIDAY 12pm - 7:15pm ','Camille de Niese','','inherit','open','open','','62-revision-4','','','2009-10-06 23:32:33','2009-10-06 13:32:33','',62,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/62-revision-4',0,'revision','',0),(179,1,'2010-02-20 18:40:43','2010-02-20 08:40:43','Dip.H.Sc. in Remedial Therapy\nDip. Anatomy, Physiology &amp; Massage [London]\nITEC Dip Massage [London]\nAAMT, ANTA, AKA (student member), Network Fitness\n\nWEDNESDAY 12pm - 7:15pm\nTHURSDAY 12pm - 7:15pm\nFRIDAY 12pm - 7:15pm\n\nCamille has a background in dance (ballet, contemporary &amp; African dance) and sport (netball) and understands the difficulty in overcoming injuries while still being able to keep up with ones physical and lifestyle pursuits. It is this background and her own struggles with injury that lead to Camille becoming a physical therapist.\n\nCamille de Niese has been working in the field of manual therapy for 13 years and has attained qualifications and skills in remedial therapy, massage, kinesiology, manual lymphatic drainage, cupping, neurostructural integration, reiki and pilates instruction.\n\nHaving worked primarily in the structural field of therapy Camille has seen first hand the extent to which our emotions and stress levels impact on us physically causing pain, stiffness and ill health. Often a purely physical approach to treatment is limited and achieving a full and lasting recovery is prolonged due to not fully resolving the primary cause of ill health. This realisation resulted in Camille undertaking further study in Kinesiology which looks at our emotional, energetic, spiritual and physical health.\n\nRemedial Kinesiology is Camille\'s combination of remedial therapy and kinesiology to provide the client with a treatment that deals with the physical, emotional, energetic and spiritual blocks to good health and well being. Through the use of kinesiology Camille is able to determine the priority issue to be dealt with in any given session and works toward restoring balance on all levels.\n\nCamille offers a variety of single therapy treatments including deep tissue massage, remedial therapy, lymphatic drainage and kinesiology as well as remedial kinesiology which provides a truly holistic treatment plan for those clients seeking to work towards resolving more long standing physical and emotional negative patterns, by incorporating a variety of therapies, treatment techniques and rehab exercises to resolve dysfunction at the root cause not just treat the symptoms.','Camille de Niese','','inherit','open','open','','62-autosave','','','2010-02-20 18:40:43','2010-02-20 08:40:43','',62,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/62-autosave',0,'revision','',0),(180,1,'2009-10-17 17:44:17','2009-10-17 07:44:17','[caption id=\"attachment_103\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"391\" caption=\"Dr Shari Trimble\"]<a href=\"/practitioners/shari\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-103\" title=\"Dr Shari Trimble\" src=\"http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/shari.jpg\" alt=\"Dr Shari Trimble\" width=\"391\" height=\"503\" /></a>[/caption]','Practioners','','inherit','open','open','','43-revision-5','','','2009-10-17 17:44:17','2009-10-17 07:44:17','',43,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/43-revision-5',0,'revision','',0),(181,1,'2009-10-17 17:56:22','2009-10-17 07:56:22','<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-176\" src=\"http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/sarah.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"232\" height=\"251\" />profile coming soon...','Sarah Valentini','','inherit','open','open','','173-revision-4','','','2009-10-17 17:56:22','2009-10-17 07:56:22','',173,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/173-revision-4',0,'revision','',0),(182,1,'2009-10-17 18:04:07','2009-10-17 08:04:07','<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-310\" title=\"Anna-Mai\" src=\"http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/Anna-Mai-website2.JPG\" alt=\"Anna-Mai\" width=\"234\" height=\"351\" />MONDAY 11am-7pm\r\nTUESDAY 11am-7pm\r\nTHURSDAY 11am-7pm\r\n<h3>Background</h3>\r\nAnna-Mai Hoek is recent graduate of the Australian College of Natural Medicine (now Endeavour College of Natural Health) and has been a valued practitioner of Dynamic Body Therapy for the last year. Anna-Mais friendly, enthusiastic nature, skill and genuine desire to help others ensures her clients are always well looked after and come away from her treatments uplifted, relieved and restored.\r\n<h3>What is Remedial Therapy?</h3>\r\nRemedial therapy is commonly understood by most to be a form of deep tissue massage to relieve aches and pains. This is a common misconception. While remedial therapy can include deep tissue massage it actually encompasses a whole range of direct and indirect techniques to remedy the physical ailments of the body to relieve tension, pain, stress, discomfort and ache, thereby improving circulation and restoring soft tissue health and function.\r\n<h3>These can include;</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Myofascial release</li>\r\n	<li>Muscle energy technique</li>\r\n	<li>Lymphatic drainage</li>\r\n	<li>Deep tissue massage/manipulation</li>\r\n	<li>Sports injury massage/management</li>\r\n	<li>Trigger point therapy</li>\r\n	<li>Relaxation techniques</li>\r\n	<li>Positional Release</li>\r\n	<li>Gentle mobilisation of structures</li>\r\n	<li>Myofascial cupping</li>\r\n	<li>Stretch/Strengthening prescription</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Therapist Goal</h3>\r\nAs a therapist I encourage my clients to view their treatment as a key segment of a greater view to promoting, within themselves, a proactive, holistic sense of health and wellbeing.\r\n\r\nAnna-Mais role in this is to restore the soft tissues of the body and address physical imbalances that may arise due to poor posture, injury, overuse or other damaging activities of daily living. Just as one must take control of their health on a holistic level, so too the soft tissues of the body must be looked upon not as a singular structure but viewed as a series of parts that all interconnect, interrelate and effect each other. Anna-Mais goal is not only to treat a symptom or dysfunction but to identify its cause so as to decrease its impact on the client or eradicate the problem altogether.\r\n\r\nAs well as feeling better physically my clients often report a feeling of relaxation and calm and an enhanced sense of mental an emotional wellbeing, an important piece of each individuals personal health jigsaw puzzle.\r\n\r\nServices Offered:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/services/remedial-massage\">Remedial Massage Therapy</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Anna-Mai Hoek','','publish','open','open','','anna-mai-hoek','','','2010-02-20 19:29:23','2010-02-20 09:29:23','',43,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/?page_id=182',5,'page','',0),(183,1,'2009-10-17 18:03:31','2009-10-17 08:03:31','','Anna-Mai Hoek','','inherit','open','open','','182-revision','','','2009-10-17 18:03:31','2009-10-17 08:03:31','',182,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/182-revision',0,'revision','',0),(184,1,'2009-10-17 18:04:07','2009-10-17 08:04:07','','Anna-Mai Hoek','','inherit','open','open','','182-revision-2','','','2009-10-17 18:04:07','2009-10-17 08:04:07','',182,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/182-revision-2',0,'revision','',0),(320,1,'2009-10-17 20:27:09','2009-10-17 10:27:09','<h3><strong>What is osteopathy? </strong></h3>\r\nOsteopathy is a holistic based treatment using the hands to correct tissue &amp; joint abnormalities. It is aimed at restoring physical &amp; mental wellbeing and thereby making it easier for the body to use its own recuperative powers to heal itself. The treatment goal is to improve circulation, reduce muscle spasm, improve flexibility, maintain nerve supply &amp; restore muscle/joint harmony\r\n<h3><strong>What kinds of problems can osteopathy help with? </strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Lower back pain, neck pain, &amp; other joint complaints</li>\r\n	<li>Headaches and migraines</li>\r\n	<li>Arthritic conditions</li>\r\n	<li>Sporting injuries such as tendonitis and strains, and stress-related muscle pain</li>\r\n	<li>Pregnancy-care for a great pregnancy and labour preparation</li>\r\n	<li>Treatment of babies and children</li>\r\n	<li>Digestive complaints such as reflux, constipation, IBS</li>\r\n	<li>Asthma and other breathing difficulties</li>\r\n	<li>And many more</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>How does osteopathy work? </strong></h3>\r\n<h4>Manipulative Osteopathy</h4>\r\nIs a whole body system of manual medicine, based on unique biomechanical principles. The osteopath uses a wide range of techniques such as\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Massage and stretching techniques</li>\r\n	<li>Articulation techniques, in which joints are mobilised by being passively taken through their range of motion</li>\r\n	<li>Muscle Energy techniques, in which contracted muscles are released by alternately being stretched and made to work against resistance.</li>\r\n	<li>Positional Release Techniques, which achieve release of restriction by placing the affected joint or muscle in a position of comfort, while applying a stretching release to the opposing muscles.</li>\r\n	<li>Functional techniques, which involve gentle mobilisation of joints in a way which \"nudges\" barriers to normal movement until a way is found through the restriction</li>\r\n	<li>Manipulation, which may be used where it is appropriate and safe to do so, though it is not the mainstay of most Osteopathic treatments. Osteopathic manipulations are carried out using minimum force levels in order to maximise safety and minimise patient discomfort</li>\r\n	<li>Visceral techniques are used in the management of conditions affecting internal organs. These involve gentle and rhythmical stretching of the visceral areas</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><strong>Biodynamic Osteopathy</strong></h4>\r\nBiodynamic osteopaths are trained to feel a very subtle, rhythmical change that is present in all body tissues. Known as primary respiratory motion, this intuitive force is capable of restoring health in the patient. Through disciplined study and a refined sense of touch, the Osteopath is able to sense and cooperate with the intention of these forces to promote healing in the patient.<a href=\"/services/biodynamic-cranial-osteopathy\"> read more</a>\r\n<h3><strong>What can I expect when I visit an osteopath? </strong></h3>\r\nWhen you visit an osteopath for the first time a full case history will be taken and you will be taken through a physical examination. You will normally be asked to remove some of your clothing and to perform a simple series of movements. The osteopath will then use a highly developed sense of touch to identify any areas of tension, weakness or altered movement throughout the body.\r\n\r\nThe osteopath may need to request additional investigations such as x-ray or blood tests. This will allow a full diagnosis and suitable treatment plan to be developed for you.\r\n<h3><strong>Can I have osteopathy on my private medical insurance or Medicare? </strong></h3>\r\nMany private health insurance schemes give benefit for osteopathic treatment. Some companies will reimburse the total fee or pay a percentage of the costs. Contact your insurance company who will explain the actual benefits and methods of claim for your individual policy. Our clinic has HICAPS which allows for claims to be made on the spot.\r\n\r\nIf you are claiming your treatment on Medicare as part of an Extended Primary Care (EPC) scheme you must have the relevant documentation from your GP prior to your first visit.\r\n\r\nStaff:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Shari Trimble\" href=\"/practitioners/shari\">Dr Shari Trimble</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/practitioners/paul\">Dr Paul Turner</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/practitioners/annabel\">Dr Annabel Eastham</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Osteopathy','','inherit','open','open','','7-revision-20','','','2009-10-17 20:27:09','2009-10-17 10:27:09','',7,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/7-revision-20',0,'revision','',0),(188,1,'2009-10-17 18:05:43','2009-10-17 08:05:43','<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-315\" title=\"Paul Turner\" src=\"http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/Paul-website.JPG\" alt=\"Paul Turner\" width=\"272\" height=\"407\" />Dr Paul Turner\r\nRegistered Osteopath, Biodynamic Craniosacral Osteopath,\r\nB.App.Sc.(Osteopathy), Member of the A.O.A\r\n\r\nMONDAY 8am  1pm\r\nSATURDAY 9am  1pm\r\n\r\nPaul has had over 15 years of experience in Cranio-sacral and Biodynamic Osteopathy as well as multi-dimensional healing methods. This form of healing work is gentle and effective in recovery from dys-function and in improving overall health and well being.\r\n\r\nCommon problems responding well to this form of treatment include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Difficulties      throughout pregnancy</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> Infants      and children with a wide range of problems such as colic, reflux,      hyperactivity, some behavioral troubles and pain</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> Any      acute or chronic pattern of pain</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> Headaches</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> Whiplash</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> Sporting      and work related injuries</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nBecause all aspects of being are addressed, this type of work can compliment other modalities of treatment by providing support in recovery from general life stresses, fatigue and some organ system dysfunctions such as irritable bowel, asthma, insomnia, menstrual pain, lymphatic congestion, etc.\r\n\r\nAs treatment is only one component of the healing process, Paul will also help you to learn effective methods of self healing and rehabilitation. This enables you to develop a deeper awareness about your own being and learn how to raise your own level of health. It also helps to avoid unnecessary repetitive visits to therapists for treatment.\r\n\r\nBecause Paul gets you involved in your own healing process, and supports the bodys self healing mechanisms in treatment, good success can be achieved in recovery from conditions that are typically slow or unresponsive to traditional treatment method\r\n\r\nServices Offered:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/services/osteopathy\">Osteopathy</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/services/biodynamic-cranial-osteopathy\">Biodynamic Osteopathy</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Paul Turner','','publish','open','open','','paul-turner','','','2011-02-12 22:57:14','2011-02-12 12:57:14','',43,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/?page_id=188',7,'page','',0),(189,1,'2009-10-17 18:05:34','2009-10-17 08:05:34','','Paul Turner','','inherit','open','open','','188-revision','','','2009-10-17 18:05:34','2009-10-17 08:05:34','',188,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/188-revision',0,'revision','',0),(190,1,'2009-10-17 18:05:43','2009-10-17 08:05:43','','Paul Turner','','inherit','open','open','','188-revision-2','','','2009-10-17 18:05:43','2009-10-17 08:05:43','',188,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/188-revision-2',0,'revision','',0),(191,1,'2009-10-17 17:36:54','2009-10-17 07:36:54','<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-166\" src=\"http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/09/cranial-girl.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"170\" height=\"220\" />Biodynamic Osteopathy is a gentle approach to Osteopathic principles and the patient, which places particular emphasis on the spirit, health, and intelligence that is experienced when the patient is understood and perceived as a whole. Biodynamic osteopaths are trained to feel a very subtle, rhythmical change that is present in all body tissues. Known as primary respiratory motion, this intuitive force is capable of restoring health in the patient. Through disciplined study and a refined sense of touch, the Osteopath is able to sense and cooperate with the intention of these forces to promote healing in the patient.\r\n\r\nTo treat the practitioner gently places their hands on your body and adds to their traditional postural assessment an assessment of the whole being using the inner life rhythms as a diagnostic tool. This enables the practitioner to assess the inner health and function of all organs and tissues of the body and also to gain an understanding of how other levels of being (energetic, emotional, mental and spiritual) are influencing the health and wellbeing of the individual assessed.\r\n\r\nTogether with traditional methods of treatment such as manipulation, articulation and soft tissue therapy (which can still be used where appropriate), biodynamic Osteopathy helps to enhance long term health in patients with a wider variety of health issues.\r\n\r\nFor more information on this type of therapy, please call and speak to one of our Osteopaths.','Biodynamic/Cranial Osteopathy','','inherit','open','open','','28-revision-9','','','2009-10-17 17:36:54','2009-10-17 07:36:54','',28,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/28-revision-9',0,'revision','',0),(192,1,'2009-10-06 20:51:59','2009-10-06 10:51:59','Remedial therapy aims to treat the primary cause of one\'s pain and dysfunction and assist the body\'s natural healing process through the use of various soft tissue techniques including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> deep tissue and sports massage</li>\r\n	<li> trigger point therapy</li>\r\n	<li> myofascial release</li>\r\n	<li> joint mobilisation</li>\r\n	<li> stretching</li>\r\n	<li> exercise prescription</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nPostural assessment and orthopaedic testing may be used to help gain insight into the possible causes of one\'s condition. In addition, complimentary therapies such as lymphatic drainage, cupping and touch for health may be used to provide a holistic approach to treatment encompassing the mind, body and spirit connection.','Remedial Massage','','inherit','open','open','','21-revision-7','','','2009-10-06 20:51:59','2009-10-06 10:51:59','',21,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/21-revision-7',0,'revision','',0),(193,1,'2009-10-17 18:13:08','2009-10-17 08:13:08','','Kinesiology','','publish','open','open','','kinesiology','','','2009-10-17 18:13:08','2009-10-17 08:13:08','',32,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/?page_id=193',3,'page','',0),(194,1,'2009-10-17 18:12:57','2009-10-17 08:12:57','','Kinesiology','','inherit','open','open','','193-revision','','','2009-10-17 18:12:57','2009-10-17 08:12:57','',193,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/193-revision',0,'revision','',0),(195,1,'2009-10-17 18:13:41','2009-10-17 08:13:41','','Acupuncture/Chinese Medicine','','publish','open','open','','acupuncturetcm','','','2009-10-17 22:09:51','2009-10-17 12:09:51','',32,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/?page_id=195',4,'page','',0),(196,1,'2009-10-17 18:13:30','2009-10-17 08:13:30','','Acupuncture/TCM','','inherit','open','open','','195-revision','','','2009-10-17 18:13:30','2009-10-17 08:13:30','',195,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/195-revision',0,'revision','',0),(197,1,'2009-10-17 18:14:05','2009-10-17 08:14:05','Naturopathy works from within by harnessing your bodys own natural  healing resources to alleviate illness. A naturopath will not only treat  your presenting symptoms but will also endeavour to diagnose and treat  the underlying cause of disease. Our approach is holistic. We do not  pursue treatment until we have made a thorough investigation into your  well-being as an individual. Once we have an understanding of your  overall health, we pursue a therapeutic strategy that includes remedies  to stimulate and aid the bodys resources in recovery as well as to  prevent the likelihood of reoccurrence. Naturopathic prescriptions  include herbal tinctures, practitioner only nutritional supplements  and herbal products. We also provide counseling on basic diet and  lifestyle.\r\n\r\nA core belief of naturopathy is that health is more than just the  absence of disease. Health is when all aspects of your mental/emotional,  biochemical and physical being are in balance. Our mandate is to make  you well. Occasionally, this may mean recognizing the limitations of  natural medicine and referring you to orthodox treatment.\r\n\r\nAnother key role of the naturopath is to educate. When you come to us  with an illness, we will educate you about your condition and provide  information on how to take care of yourself.\r\n<h2>How Can Naturopathy Help You and Your Family?</h2>\r\nNaturopathy offers a broad spectrum of alternative treatments from  preventative healthcare through to treatment for serious, chronic  debilitating disease. We provide safe and effective therapy for children  and adults to manage a range of conditions including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Colds, flu and upper respiratory infections</li>\r\n	<li>Asthma</li>\r\n	<li>Eczema, psoriasis and other skin conditions</li>\r\n	<li>Stress</li>\r\n	<li>Depression/anxiety</li>\r\n	<li>Insomnia</li>\r\n	<li>Headaches/migraines</li>\r\n	<li>Chronic fatigue syndrome</li>\r\n	<li>Menopause</li>\r\n	<li>Menstrual irregularities and pain</li>\r\n	<li>Diabetes</li>\r\n	<li>Obesity</li>\r\n	<li>Anorexia</li>\r\n	<li>Cardiovascular disease</li>\r\n	<li>Coeliac disease</li>\r\n	<li>Digestive difficulties</li>\r\n	<li>Cancer/HIV</li>\r\n	<li>Hayfever/sinusitis</li>\r\n	<li>Infertility, IVF assistance</li>\r\n	<li>Preconception, natal care</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nPractitioners:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/practitioners/anne\">Anne Howard</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Naturopathy','','publish','open','open','','naturopathy','','','2011-03-10 20:07:22','2011-03-10 10:07:22','',32,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/?page_id=197',5,'page','',0),(198,1,'2009-10-17 18:13:56','2009-10-17 08:13:56','','Naturopathy','','inherit','open','open','','197-revision','','','2009-10-17 18:13:56','2009-10-17 08:13:56','',197,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/197-revision',0,'revision','',0),(199,1,'2009-10-17 17:42:49','2009-10-17 07:42:49','Here are our services:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/services/osteopathy\">Osteopathy</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Services','','inherit','open','open','','32-revision-16','','','2009-10-17 17:42:49','2009-10-17 07:42:49','',32,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/u