ibed in conjunction with the patient\'s raw herbs when traveling or boiling preparation may be inconvenient.\r\n<h3><strong>Cupping</strong></h3>\r\nDr Eddy has used Cupping Therapy effectively to help heal chronically sore muscles, old sports injuries, as well as a gentle remedy to clear or prevent common colds and flu. Cupping has received a lot of media attention as the trendy therapy of choice by celebrities in recent years. However, this ancient therapy that has been used for thousands of years in Asia and Europe. It involves the application of heated glass cups that vacuum seal on the skin, which draws stagnant blood and metabolites (such as pain chemicals) to the surface of the body. Many patients express a pleasant feeling of deep relaxation in receiving this gentle but powerful form of treatment.\r\n\r\nServices Offered:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/services/acupuncturetcm\">Acupuncture/Chinese Medicine</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Chris Eddy','','inherit','open','open','','136-revision-12','','','2010-02-20 19:17:35','2010-02-20 09:17:35','',136,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/136-revision-12',0,'revision','',0),(308,1,'2010-02-20 19:20:35','2010-02-20 09:20:35','','Anna-Mai','','inherit','open','open','','anna-mai-website','','','2010-02-20 19:20:35','2010-02-20 09:20:35','',182,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/Anna-Mai-website.JPG',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(309,1,'2010-02-20 19:23:11','2010-02-20 09:23:11','','Anna-Mai - website','','inherit','open','open','','anna-mai-website-2','','','2010-02-20 19:23:11','2010-02-20 09:23:11','',182,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/Anna-Mai-website1.JPG',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(310,1,'2010-02-20 19:26:04','2010-02-20 09:26:04','','Anna-Mai','','inherit','open','open','','anna-mai-website-3','','','2010-02-20 19:26:04','2010-02-20 09:26:04','',182,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/Anna-Mai-website2.JPG',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(311,1,'2009-10-27 12:04:27','2009-10-27 02:04:27','MONDAY 11am-7pm\r\nTUESDAY 11am-7pm\r\nTHURSDAY 11am-7pm\r\n<h3>Background</h3>\r\nAnna-Mai Hoek is recent graduate of the Australian College of Natural Medicine (now Endeavour College of Natural Health) and has been a valued practitioner of Dynamic Body Therapy for the last year. Anna-Mais friendly, enthusiastic nature, skill and genuine desire to help others ensures her clients are always well looked after and come away from her treatments uplifted, relieved and restored.\r\n<h3>What is Remedial Therapy?</h3>\r\nRemedial therapy is commonly understood by most to be a form of deep tissue massage to relieve aches and pains. This is a common misconception. While remedial therapy can include deep tissue massage it actually encompasses a whole range of direct and indirect techniques to remedy the physical ailments of the body to relieve tension, pain, stress, discomfort and ache, thereby improving circulation and restoring soft tissue health and function.\r\n<h3>These can include;</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Myofascial release</li>\r\n	<li>Muscle energy technique</li>\r\n	<li>Lymphatic drainage</li>\r\n	<li>Deep tissue massage/manipulation</li>\r\n	<li>Sports injury massage/management</li>\r\n	<li>Trigger point therapy</li>\r\n	<li>Relaxation techniques</li>\r\n	<li>Positional Release</li>\r\n	<li>Gentle mobilisation of structures</li>\r\n	<li>Myofascial cupping</li>\r\n	<li>Stretch/Strengthening prescription</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Therapist Goal</h3>\r\nAs a therapist I encourage my clients to view their treatment as a key segment of a greater view to promoting, within themselves, a proactive, holistic sense of health and wellbeing.\r\n\r\nAnna-Mais role in this is to restore the soft tissues of the body and address physical imbalances that may arise due to poor posture, injury, overuse or other damaging activities of daily living. Just as one must take control of their health on a holistic level, so too the soft tissues of the body must be looked upon not as a singular structure but viewed as a series of parts that all interconnect, interrelate and effect each other. Anna-Mais goal is not only to treat a symptom or dysfunction but to identify its cause so as to decrease its impact on the client or eradicate the problem altogether.\r\n\r\nAs well as feeling better physically my clients often report a feeling of relaxation and calm and an enhanced sense of mental an emotional wellbeing, an important piece of each individuals personal health jigsaw puzzle.\r\n\r\nServices Offered:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/services/remedial-massage\">Remedial Massage Therapy</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Anna-Mai Hoek','','inherit','open','open','','182-revision-6','','','2009-10-27 12:04:27','2009-10-27 02:04:27','',182,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/182-revision-6',0,'revision','',0),(312,1,'2010-02-20 19:31:47','2010-02-20 09:31:47','','Annabel Eastham','','inherit','open','open','','annabel-website','','','2010-02-20 19:31:47','2010-02-20 09:31:47','',43,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/Annabel-website.JPG',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(323,1,'2009-10-17 18:23:11','2009-10-17 08:23:11','<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Acupuncture/ Chinese Herbal Medicine</span></h3>\r\nInitial Consultation (1 Hour) $90\r\nSubsequent Treatment (45 minutes) $70\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Lymphatic Drainage/ Massage - Deep Tissue/ Relaxation/ Remedial</span></h3>\r\n30 minutes $45\r\n45 minutes $60\r\n60 minutes $75\r\n90 minutes $100\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Naturopathy</span></h3>\r\nInitial consult 1hr $90\r\nFollow up appts $60\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Osteopathy</span></h3>\r\nInitial Consultation (1 Hour) $90\r\nSubsequent Treatment (45 minutes) $70\r\n\r\nConsultations can include a combination of treatments where appropriate\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Health Insurance Rebate</span></h3>\r\nAcupunctu