hes</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> Whiplash</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> Sporting      and work related injuries</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nBecause all aspects of being are addressed, this type of work can compliment other modalities of treatment by providing support in recovery from general life stresses, fatigue and some organ system dysfunctions such as irritable bowel, asthma, insomnia, menstrual pain, lymphatic congestion, etc.\r\n\r\nAs treatment is only one component of the healing process, Paul will also help you to learn effective methods of self healing and rehabilitation. This enables you to develop a deeper awareness about your own being and learn how to raise your own level of health. It also helps to avoid unnecessary repetitive visits to therapists for treatment.\r\n\r\nBecause Paul gets you involved in your own healing process, and supports the bodys self healing mechanisms in treatment, good success can be achieved in recovery from conditions that are typically slow or unresponsive to traditional treatment method\r\n\r\nServices Offered:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/services/osteopathy\">Osteopathy</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/services/biodynamic-cranial-osteopathy\">Biodynamic Osteopathy</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Paul Turner','','inherit','open','open','','188-revision-5','','','2010-02-20 20:11:59','2010-02-20 10:11:59','',188,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/188-revision-5',0,'revision','',0),(318,1,'2010-03-05 11:32:49','2010-03-05 01:32:49','<div><strong>Dynamic Body Therapy has a very experienced team of professional therapists dedicated to excellence in health care and wellbeing. All of our practitioners are trained to the highest standards and registered with the required professional body governing their practice. We offer a broad range of therapies including Osteopathy, Kinesiology, Remedial Massage, Naturopathy, Acupuncture and Traditional Chinese Medicine.</strong></div>\n<strong>\n\n</strong>','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','235-autosave','','','2010-03-05 11:32:49','2010-03-05 01:32:49','',235,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/235-autosave',0,'revision','',0),(319,1,'2009-10-17 21:54:37','2009-10-17 11:54:37','[caption id=\"attachment_103\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"222\" caption=\"Dr Shari Trimble\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-103\" title=\"Dr Shari Trimble\" src=\"http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/shari.jpg\" alt=\"Dr Shari Trimble\" width=\"222\" height=\"285\" />[/caption]\r\n\r\nDr Shari Trimble\r\nOsteopath, Biodynamic Osteopath, Prescriptive Exercise Consultant\r\nM.H.Sc. [Osteo], B.Sc [Clin], M.A.O.A\r\n\r\nMONDAY 1pm - 7pm\r\nWEDNESDAY 1pm - 7pm\r\nFRIDAY 1pm - 6pm\r\n\r\nShari is the co owner of the practice with Camille de Niese. She has worked in the health and manual medicine field for more than 15 years and also lectures in anatomy, pathology and clinical skills.\r\n\r\nSharis passion is to assist in helping the body\'s own wisdom restore health and balance. With a nurturing and gentle style, Shari tailors her treatments to each individual, working to stimulate the body\'s natural ability to heal itself.\r\n<h3><strong>Special Interest in Yoga and Performance Arts</strong></h3>\r\nWith her past experience in engineering, a Bachelor degree in Clinical Science and a Masters in Osteopathy, Shari has a thorough understanding of body mechanics and a unique capacity to view your injury in the context of activity and training. Shari focuses on helping you to rehabilitate your injury whilst continuing to practice and train, and how to avoid further disruption to your program.\r\n\r\nCurrently a member of the Footscray Womens Circus Shari also runs her dogs and practices yoga daily. She has a background in dance, pilates and long distance running and has completed postgraduate studies in exercise prescription &amp; clinical pilates.\r\n<h3><strong>Special Interests in Womens Health, Fertility &amp; Children</strong></h3>\r\nShari has completed post graduate osteopathic studies in obstetrics &amp; gynaecology and the treatment of children and enjoys working with the challenges women may face during pregnancy and motherhood.\r\n<h3><strong><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-255\" src=\"http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/pregnancy.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"266\" height=\"266\" />Pregnancy</strong></h3>\r\nDuring pregnancy there are many physiological processes that take place and large changes to a womens body occur in a relatively short space of time. A hormone called Relaxin softens the ligaments around the joints of the pelvis which is a natural process and assists childbirth. However for some women this process can cause the joints of the pelvis to loosen too much and can result in the pelvis becoming unstable or out of alignment and in a susceptible women can contribute to low back and pelvic pain.\r\n\r\nPost pregnancy there will be pressure on different areas such as the upper back and neck. This may be due to poor posture during breast feeding and incorrect lifting techniques. Osteopathic treatment and corrective muscle re-education can aid in the way the body copes with these pressures.\r\n<h3><strong>Babies &amp; Children</strong></h3>\r\nA baby will often communicate there is a problem by being unsettled, irritable or wakeful. Symptoms in a newborn baby to be aware of are:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Colic</li>\r\n	<li>excessive wind</li>\r\n	<li>continuous crying</li>\r\n	<li>difficulty feeding or a preference to feed from one breast</li>\r\n	<li>sleeping difficulties</li>\r\n	<li>stiffness of the neck muscles</li>\r\n	<li>favouring the head to one side</li>\r\n	<li>a misshapen head</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-257\" src=\"http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/osteopathy-for-infants1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"228\" height=\"235\" />Biodynamic/Cranial Osteopathy can be useful in treating a wide range of symptoms and conditions in children including the following\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>back and neck pain</li>\r\n	<li>ear infections and glue ear</li>\r\n	<li>growing pains</li>\r\n	<li>headaches</li>\r\n	<li>behavioural problems</li>\r\n	<li>hyperactivity</li>\r\n	<li>speech problems</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nServices Offered:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Read About Osteopathy\" href=\"/services/osteopathy\">Osteopathy</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/services/biodynamic-cranial-osteopathy\">Biodynamics/Cranial Osteopathy</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Shari Trimble','','inherit','open','open','','45-revision-21','','','2009-10-17 21:54:37','2009-10-17 11:54:37','',45,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/45-revision-21',0,'revision','',0),(329,1,'2010-02-20 20:16:07','2010-02-20 10:16:07','<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-315\" title=\"Paul Turner\" src=\"http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/Paul-website.JPG\" alt=\"Paul Turner\" width=\"272\" height=\"407\" />Dr Paul Turner\r\nOsteopath, Biodynamic Osteopath,\r\nB.App.Sc.(Osteopathy), M.A.O.A\r\n\r\nMONDAY 8am  1pm\r\nSATURDAY 9am  1pm\r\n\r\nPaul has had over 15 years of experience in Cranio-sacral and Biodynamic Osteopathy as well as multi-dimensional healing methods. This form of healing work is gentle and effective in recovery from dys-function and in improving overall health and well being.\r\n\r\nCommon problems responding well to this form of treatment include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Difficulties      throughout pregnancy</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> Infants      and children with a wide range of problems such as colic, reflux,      hyperactivity, some behavioral troubles and pain</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> Any      acute or chronic pattern of pain</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> Headaches</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> Whiplash</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> Sporting      and work related injuries</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nBecause all aspects of being are addressed, this type of work can compliment other modalities of trea