 there are many physiological processes that take place and large changes to a womens body occur in a relatively short space of time. A hormone called Relaxin softens the ligaments around the joints of the pelvis which is a natural process and assists childbirth. However for some women this process can cause the joints of the pelvis to loosen too much and can result in the pelvis becoming unstable or out of alignment and in a susceptible women can contribute to low back and pelvic pain.\r\n\r\nPost pregnancy there will be pressure on different areas such as the upper back and neck. This may be due to poor posture during breast feeding and incorrect lifting techniques. Osteopathic treatment and corrective muscle re-education can aid in the way the body copes with these pressures.\r\n<h3><strong>Babies &amp; Children</strong></h3>\r\nA baby will often communicate there is a problem by being unsettled, irritable or wakeful. Symptoms in a newborn baby to be aware of are:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Colic</li>\r\n	<li>excessive wind</li>\r\n	<li>continuous crying</li>\r\n	<li>difficulty feeding or a preference to feed from one breast</li>\r\n	<li>sleeping difficulties</li>\r\n	<li>stiffness of the neck muscles</li>\r\n	<li>favouring the head to one side</li>\r\n	<li>a misshapen head</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-257\" src=\"http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/osteopathy-for-infants1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"228\" height=\"235\" />Biodynamic/Cranial Osteopathy can be useful in treating a wide range of symptoms and conditions in children including the following\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>back and neck pain</li>\r\n	<li>ear infections and glue ear</li>\r\n	<li>growing pains</li>\r\n	<li>headaches</li>\r\n	<li>behavioural problems</li>\r\n	<li>hyperactivity</li>\r\n	<li>speech problems</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nServices Offered:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Read About Osteopathy\" href=\"/services/osteopathy\">Osteopathy</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/services/biodynamic-cranial-osteopathy\">Biodynamics/Cranial Osteopathy</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Shari Trimble','','inherit','open','open','','45-revision-26','','','2011-02-12 22:56:07','2011-02-12 12:56:07','',45,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/45-revision-26',0,'revision','',0),(341,1,'2009-10-17 21:52:07','2009-10-17 11:52:07','<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-276\" src=\"http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/naturopathy.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"260\" height=\"206\" />Naturopathy is a holistic method of healing which recognises the ability of the body to overcome disease. Treatments aim to support and aid the body to heal itself with the use of herbal medicine, homeopathy, and nutritional and lifestyle advice. Naturopathy treats the underlying cause within the body to achieve optimal health that may have been compromised by lifestyle, genetic predisposition or dietary imbalances. Within this belief, naturopathy aims to restore vitality through supporting and stimulating the bodys own healing mechanisms\r\n\r\n<a href=\"/services/naturopathy\">Read More...</a>','Naturopathy','','inherit','open','open','','225-revision-4','','','2009-10-17 21:52:07','2009-10-17 11:52:07','',225,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/225-revision-4',0,'revision','',0),(342,1,'2011-03-10 20:02:18','2011-03-10 10:02:18','Anne Howard  Naturopath, Herbalist, Nutritionist\nB. H. Sc. (Naturopathy)\nDip. H. Sc. (Nutrition)\nDip. H. Sc. (Herbal Medicine)\nATMS\n<h3>Senior Lecturer  Naturopathy.</h3>\nAnne comes highly qualified as a naturopath and educator with a  degree in naturopathy, diplomas in nutrition and herbal medicine and a  background in mineral therapy, Bach flower essences, iridology and  aromatherapy. She applies this diverse knowledge with care, precision  and enthusiasm, establishing comfortable, good-humoured and constructive  relationships with each of her clients. All examinations and  consultations are tailored to your individual needs as a patient. This  commitment to your health and well-being enables Anne to provide  appropriate, effective solutions and counseling to meet your unique  needs.\n\nAnne is currently employed in a senior academic and administrative  position at the Endeavour College of Natural health where one of her  main roles is to lecture and supervise students of naturopathy. She is  also an experienced presenter of corporate health seminars.\n<h2>What is Naturopathy?</h2>\nNaturopathy works from within by harnessing your bodys own natural healing resources to alleviate illness. A naturopath will not only treat your presenting symptoms but will also endeavour to diagnose and treat the underlying cause of disease. Our approach is holistic. We do not pursue treatment until we have made a thorough investigation into your well-being as an individual. Once we have an understanding of your overall health, we pursue a therapeutic strategy that includes remedies to stimulate and aid the bodys resources in recovery as well as to prevent the likelihood of reoccurrence. Naturopathic prescriptions include herbal tinctures, practitioner only nutritional supplements and herbal products. We also provide counseling on basic diet and lifestyle.\n\nA core belief of naturopathy is that health is more than just the absence of disease. Health is when all aspects of your mental/emotional, biochemical and physical being are in balance. Our mandate is to make you well. Occasionally, this may mean recognizing the limitations of natural medicine and referring you to orthodox treatment.\n\nAnother key role of the naturopath is to educate. When you come to us with an illness, we will educate you about your condition and provide information on how to take care of yourself.\n<h2>How Can Naturopathy Help You and Your Family?</h2>\nNaturopathy offers a broad spectrum of alternative treatments from preventative healthcare through to treatment for serious, chronic debilitating disease. We provide safe and effective therapy for children and adults to manage a range of conditions including:\n<ul>\n	<li>Colds, flu and upper respiratory infections</li>\n	<li>Asthma</li>\n	<li>Eczema, psoriasis and other skin conditions</li>\n	<li>Stress</li>\n	<li>Depression/anxiety</li>\n	<li>Insomnia</li>\n	<li>Headaches/migraines</li>\n	<li>Chronic fatigue syndrome</li>\n	<li>Menopause</li>\n	<li>Menstrual irregularities and pain</li>\n	<li>Diabetes</li>\n	<li>Obesity</li>\n	<li>Anorexia</li>\n	<li>Cardiovascular disease</li>\n	<li>Coeliac disease</li>\n	<li>Digestive difficulties</li>\n	<li>Cancer/HIV</li>\n	<li>Hayfever/sinusitis</li>\n	<li>Infertility, IVF assistance</li>\n	<li>Preconception, natal care</li>\n</ul>\nServices Offered:\n<ul>\n	<li>Naturopathy</li>\n</ul>','Anne Howard','','inherit','open','open','','133-autosave','','','2011-03-10 20:02:18','2011-03-10 10:02:18','',133,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/133-autosave',0,'revision','',0),(343,1,'2009-10-07 22:44:12','2009-10-07 12:44:12','<span style=\"color: green;\">Naturopath, Herbalist, Nutritionist</span>\r\nB.H.Sc. [Nat], Dip.H.Sc. [Nut],\r\nDip.H.Sc. [Herb. Med], A.T.M.S\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: green;\">TUESDAY      11:30am - 1:00pm\r\nTHURSDAY      10:00am - 1:00pm</span>','Anne Howard','','inherit','open','open','','133-revision-3','','','2009-10-07 22:44:12','2009-10-07 12:44:12','',133,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/133-revision-3',0,'revision','',0),(345,1,'2011-02-12 22:57:46','2011-02-12 12:57:46','Dr Shari Trimble\r\nRegistered Osteopath, Biodynamic Craniosacral Osteopath, Prescriptive Exercise Consultant\r\nM.H.Sc. [Osteo], B.Sc [Clin], Member of the A.O.A\r\n\r\nMONDAY 1pm - 7pm\r\nWEDNESDAY 1pm - 7pm\r\nFRIDAY 1pm - 6pm\r\n\r\nShari is the co owner of the practice with Camille de Niese. She has worked in the health and manual medicine field for more than 15 years and also lectures in anatomy, pathology and clinical skills.\r\n\r\nSharis passion is to assist i